notes: all the tests used the Data Interoperability Extension - no out of the box support

gml_file_load.notes: File has to be renamed to EMF_BRGM_data.gml; application Schema has to be loaded; used with the Data Interoperability Extension

gml_file_display.notes: File has to be renamed to EMF_BRGM_data.gml; application Schema has to be loaded; used with the Data Interoperability Extension

gml_WFS2_load.notes: Features contain multiple geometries (geometry, representativePoint), one is used; used with the Data Interoperability Extension

gml_WFS2_display.notes: Loaded data displays, but the server returns multiple schemas for the feature: https://wfspoc.brgm-rec.fr/geoserver/wfs?SERVICE=WFS&VERSION=2.0.0&REQUEST=DescribeFeatureType&TYPENAMES=ef%3AEnvironmentalMonitoringFacility; used with the Data Interoperability Extension

gml_features_edit.notes: Direct GML editing is not supported; an ETL process is required, but during or after import features may be edited; used with the Data Interoperability Extension

gml_features_create.notes: Direct GML editing is not supported. Features of the same schema may be created in the imported dataset; an ETL process is required; used with the Data Interoperability Extension
